rhKY_so7lWo.title: Estará a agricultura na moda? Comentário Jornal 2 RTP
rhKY_so7lWo.description:
A agricultura está de volta, os agricultores, as suas práticas sustentáveis e o seu investimento são necessários, na paisagem e na sociedade contemporânea, mais do que nunca. Assim saibamos todos compreender. E ARRISCAR. É preciso arriscar para quebrar com as convenções que nos foram impingidas desde o dia em que nascemos.

O regresso às raízes é possível mas envolve sacrifício. No nosso caso, o balanço tem sido francamente positivo. Na génese de tudo isto está a partilha constante de conhecimento, fundamental na necessária confiança a adquirir pelos novos agricultores, até porque muitos não tem ainda todas as "ferramentas" necessárias, porque os novos agricultores não são agrónomos de formação, na maior parte dos casos. No entanto, há algo de "agrónomo e de médico" em cada um de nós!!! Mas não há fórmulas, tem que ser construídas de novo, meus amigos!!!

XkJFfn6avSo.title: Masanga ( instrumental ) - Jean Bosco Mwenda
XkJFfn6avSo.description:
Jean Bosco Mwenda, also known as Mwenda wa Bayeke (1930--1990) was a pioneer of Congolese fingerstyle acoustic guitar music. He was also popular in other African countries, particularly East Africa, and in the late 1950s and early 1960s was briefly based in Nairobi, where he had a regular radio show and became a profound influence on a generation of Kenyan guitarists. Along with his friend and sometime partner Losta Abelo, and his cousin Edouard Masengo, Bosco defined the Congolese acoustic guitar style. His song "Masanga" was particularly influential, due to its complex and varied guitar part. His influences included traditional music of Zambia and the Eastern Congo, Cuban groups like the Trio Matamoros, and cowboy movies. Bosco was born in 1930 at Bunkeya, a village near Likasi (then called Jadotville), Haut-Katanga Province in then Belgian Congo, but lived most of his life in Lubumbashi, where in addition to playing music he had a job in a bank and with the local mining company, managed other bands, and owned a hotel on the Zambian border. He died September 1990 in a car accident in Zambia.

A 1982 video field recording by Gerhard Kubik exists in a compilation of influential African guitarists artists entitled "Native African Guitar". A 1982 CD with booklet (text by Gerhard Kubik, also in English; includes the Kisuahili song texts) is available from Museum fÃ¼r VÃ¶lkerkunde, Berlin. The recordings include the complete concert Bosco gave at June 30, 1982 at the Museum fÃ¼r VÃ¶lkerkunde, Berlin. In 1988 Cape Town based record label, Mountain Records, recorded a studio album of Mwenda's music and issued it in 1994. The album is entitled Mwenda wa Bayeke - African guitar legend.

Please know that this is my own design and there are other ways of making a "ninja frisbee".  There are multiple ways of connecting the ninja stars so you should try to make your own design also!
